premise_source_doc_sentence: Tequila  (  Spanish  )  is a regionally specific name for a distilled beverage made from the blue agave plant , primarily in the area surrounding the city of Tequila , 65 km northwest of Guadalajara , and in the highlands  (  Los Altos  )  of the central western Mexican state of Jalisco .
